data.text:
How teenagers are trying to save Bangladesh from total collapse

new york times / Aug 13, 2024, 16:19 (IST)

The young protesters who felled an autocrat are now cabinet ministers and traffic cops, trying to restore order and chart a new future for a nation of 170mn

Why Railways is unlikely to go for aluminium Vande Bharat

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 13:28 (IST)

Indian Railways has nixed plans for aluminium-bodied Vande Bharat trains due to high costs and lack of domestic expertise. Future focus aims at cost-effective sleeper versions utilizing indigenous technology.

US may be planning to ‘break-up’ Google, firm forced to sell these businesses

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 10:39 (IST)

The US Department of Justice considered an antitrust move to break up Google after a court ruled that it monopolised online search markets. Remedies may include selling Android, Chrome, or AdWords, and sharing data with competitors. Discussions also focused on banning exclusive contracts, which pay billions to companies like Apple and Samsung.

The strange saga of theft at a poet’s home and a regretful thief

timesofindia.com / Aug 13, 2024, 19:15 (IST)

The theft at Narayan Surve’s house near Mumbai made headlines after the thief returned a TV and sought forgiveness. But there’s a deeper story that finds echoes in the poet’s work

Remove these Amul videos: Delhi High Court to YT, FB and Instagram

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 00:49 (IST)

The Delhi High Court ordered a Noida resident to remove defamatory videos about Amul products from social media. This followed a viral claim of a centipede found in an Amul ice cream tub. Non-compliance led to the court directing platforms like X, YouTube, and Meta to take down the content within 36 hours.

Vinesh Phogat's CAS appeal verdict deferred: A timeline of events

timesofindia.com / Aug 14, 2024, 13:26 (IST)

Indian wrestler Vinesh Phogat's disqualification from the Paris Olympics due to being 100 grams overweight continues pending a decision from the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS). Her appeal's verdict has been postponed thrice, causing uncertainty. Phogat, who recently announced her retirement, awaits the final ruling set for August 16.
